{"result":{"contents":[{"language":"java","value":"java.lang.Override"},"Indicates that a method declaration is intended to override a method declaration in a supertype. If a method is annotated with this annotation type compilers are required to generate an error message unless at least one of the following conditions hold:\r\n\r\n *  The method does override or implement a method declared in a supertype.\r\n *  The method has a signature that is override-equivalent to that of any public method declared in Object.\r\n\r\nSince:\r\n\r\n1.5\r\n\r\nSee  The JavaÖ Language Specification:\r\n\r\n9.6.1.4\r\n\r\n *  @Override\r\n    \r\n     *  /dd\u003e"]},"id":"1338","type":"vertex","label":"hoverResult"}
